          <aside class="tldr">
            <h2 id="key-takeaways">Key Takeaways</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>This glossary is a comprehensive reference</strong> for the terminology, methods, conditions, and procedures encountered within Restorative Reproductive Medicine (RRM).</li>
              <li><strong>Organized into eight parts:</strong> core principles, fertility awareness methods, clinical approaches (NaProTECHNOLOGY, FEMM, NeoFertility, Marquette), diagnostic tools, surgical techniques, key conditions, overlapping disciplines, and the broader RRM framework.</li>
              <li><strong>Intended for patients, students, and clinicians</strong> seeking clear, evidence-based definitions grounded in published research.</li>
              <li><strong>Use the table of contents</strong> to navigate directly to a specific section or term. An abbreviation quick-reference table is included at the end.</li>
            </ul>
